content:
From any case list page, administrators can "mass update" multiple cases at once. Users can take ownership of one or more cases if they are a member of that queue, higher in the role hierarchy than a queue member, or if the organization's default sharing for cases is Public Read/Write/Transfer.

Available in: Salesforce Classic (not available in all orgs) and Group, Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions

To change case owner:
 
* Transfer Cases OR Transfer Record
* AND
* Edit on cases
 
To close and change the status of cases:
 
* Manage Cases
 
Check the boxes next to the desired cases and click the appropriate button. The following actions are possible:

Accept—Assigns you as the owner of the selected cases in a queue list view.
Change Owner—Assigns the cases to the one user or queue you specify.
Close—Closes the selected cases using the values you specify.
Change Status—Changes the Status of the cases to the value you set.
title: Bulk Update Multiple Cases in Service Cloud
